PROPOSAL: graft-initial-2026-03-03
STATUS: pending
TIER: T1
FILE: core/graft.py
AUTHOR: Shiva (Claude Code) + Sean Campbell

SUMMARY
-------
Initial implementation of GRAFT — the task management layer.

GRAFT governs what gets done. It's the work queue for the entire system:
agents create tasks, tasks route to executors, conflicts are arbitrated by
priority, flow control handles dependencies, and every state change is logged.

DESIGN DECISIONS
----------------
1. Caller provides db_path (artifacts/{username}/graft.db). No path logic inside.
2. try/finally on every connection.
3. Priority: int 0–10. Higher = sooner. Default 5. next_task() returns highest
   priority pending task with no unresolved dependencies.
4. Governance tier tracked but not enforced here — enforcement is the caller's job.
   T1=human approval required, T2=log+auto, T3=proceed. Stored for auditability.
5. Dependency chain: task B blocked_by task A. next_task() skips blocked tasks.
6. State machine: pending → in_progress → completed | failed | cancelled
   Also: blocked (all dependencies not yet completed).
7. Audit log: every state transition logged to task_log with agent + notes.
8. FIFO within same priority: created_at ASC as tiebreaker.

PUBLIC API
----------
init_tables(db_path) → None

create(db_path, username, subject, description, agent,
       priority=5, tier=2, metadata=None) → str  # returns task_id

get(db_path, task_id) → Optional[dict]
list_tasks(db_path, username, agent=None, status=None, limit=50) → list[dict]
update(db_path, task_id, status, agent, notes=None) → bool
cancel(db_path, task_id, agent, reason=None) → bool
delete(db_path, task_id) → bool

next_task(db_path, username, agent) → Optional[dict]
add_dependency(db_path, task_id, blocked_by_id) → None
get_log(db_path, task_id) → list[dict]
stats(db_path, username, agent=None) → dict

SCHEMA
------
tasks     — (task_id TEXT PK, username, subject, description, status,
             agent, priority INT, tier INT, created_at, updated_at,
             completed_at, metadata TEXT)
task_deps — (task_id, blocked_by_id, PRIMARY KEY(task_id, blocked_by_id))
task_log  — (id, task_id, timestamp, action, agent, notes)

